    """<p class="eq-p">Analyst revisions are a sentiment thermometer, not a guarantee. When estimates for {t0} drift, ask whether the change reflects new data or herd reshuffling after price moved. Primary-source readers can sometimes spot when the revision cycle is running ahead of fundamentals—or lagging badly after a filing inflection.</p>""",
